---
import ProjectLayout from "../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro";
import img1 from '../../assets/Mech_Design_1.png';
import img2 from '../../assets/Mech_Design_2.png';

const projectSpecs = [
  { label: "Location", value: "Purdue University" },
  { label: "Dates", value: "April 2025" },
  { label: "Course", value: "THTR 550 Mechanical Design for the Stage" },
  { label: "Skills", value: "Mechanical Concept Design, FMEA, Stakeholder Identification" }
];
---

<ProjectLayout 
    title="Mechanical Design for the Stage"
    subtitle="Coursework in Mechanical Design for Theatre and Entertainment"
    images={[img1, img2]}
    specs={projectSpecs}>

    <h2>Overview</h2>
    
    <p>
        This course featured a final project to design a mechanical system to raise and lower a cantilevered
        ceiling spanning a stage, with movements from 30 to 60 degrees from horizontal occurring across 15 minutes.
        At some point near the end of the show, the ceiling would need to 'come crashing down' as if the sky were falling.   
    </p> 

    <p>
        For this project, I developed a stage winch drive system to create the effect. For the 'crash' to occur, I
        designed a disconnect system, where the ceiling panel can be disconnected from the winch. In order to allow
        the ceiling to come falling down safely, I implemented an Eddy current braking system, similar to those seen 
        on fail-safe roller coaster brake runs. This would slow the wall naturally while falling, giving it a smooth yet
        sudden deceleration to look as though it were caught. 
    </p>

    <!--
    <p>
        Displayed above are images of the CAD model as well as documentation including a BOM, FMEA, and 
    </p>
    -->
</ProjectLayout>



<style is:global>
    .video-frame {
        width: 100%;
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 2rem auto;
        border-radius: 8px;
        background: #000; /* Mimics the dark theater behind the screen */
        padding: 10px; /* Creates a small "letterbox" frame */
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        transition: border-color 0.4s ease, box-shadow 0.4s ease;
    }

    .video-frame:hover {
        border-color: var(--accent-orange);
        box-shadow: 0 0 20px var(--accent-glow);
    }
    
    .project-hero-img {
        width: 100%;
        height: 600px;
    }

    h2 {
        margin-top: -0.8rem;
    }

    video.film-glow {
        width: 100%;
        display: block;
        border-radius: 4px;
        /* Cinematic color grade: slight contrast boost */
        filter: contrast(1.1) saturate(0.9);
    }
</style>